  - abstract: It is shown that the global charges of a gauge theory may yield a
      nontrivial central extension of the asymptotic symmetry algebra already at
      the classical level. This is done by studying three dimensional gravity
      with a negative cosmological constant. The asymptotic symmetry group in
      that case is eitherR×SO(2) or the pseudo-conformal group in two
      dimensions, depending on the boundary conditions adopted at spatial
      infinity. In the latter situation, a nontrivial central charge appears in
      the algebra of the canonical generators, which turns out to be just the
      Virasoro central charge.
