  - abstract: We study toroidal compactification of Matrix theory, using ideas and
      results of non-commutative geometry. We generalize this to
      compactification on the noncommutative torus, explain the classification
      of these backgrounds, and argue that they correspond in supergravity to
      tori with constant background three-form tensor field. The paper includes
      an introduction for mathematicians to the IKKT formulation of Matrix
      theory and its relation to the BFSS Matrix theory.
